## Hamza's Progress (3D Printing Simulation)

This section explains the 3D printing simulation and preparation of the robotic arm parts using IdeaMaker. All components were sliced and evaluated in terms of print time, material consumption, support requirements, and overall printability.

The analysis showed clear differences between the parts. The base and shoulder experience the highest torque and therefore require stronger print settings. The elbow experiences moderate torque, while the gripper experiences the lowest torque and can be printed with lighter requirements.

The design work focused on validating all parts before fabrication, improving slicing settings, and preparing the files for printing and assembly.

